## v1.0.0 (2026-06-19)

**Initial version.** Planning-discipline learning from the first plan for GitHub issue #184
(Odysseus e2e NATS crash-reconnect placeholder test). Established the core rule that a fault
test must be able to go RED, prove recovery by an observable end-to-end effect, and use a clean
SKIP (never a pass) where the fault is structurally inapplicable — plus a catalog of the
unverified assumptions a planner makes when writing such a plan without running code.

